Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.11,0:00:06.98,Default - italics,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,The year 850, in Trost...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.89,0:00:10.35,Default - italics,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,The sight of Eren Jaeger unleashing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.35,0:00:12.03,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,the power of a mysterious Titan
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.61,0:00:16.89,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,was more than enough to \Nterrify his fellow soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.10,0:00:22.26,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I am a human!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.31,0:00:25.46,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,He is not an enemy of humanity!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.50,0:00:28.71,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,With my final breath before my death,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.71,0:00:31.46,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,I shall wish for humanity's glory,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.46,0:00:34.28,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,and try to persuade you \Nof his strategic value!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.94,0:00:41.89,Default - italics,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,As Eren and his friends could do nothing \Nbut argue their innocence,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.38,0:00:44.00,Default - italics,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,they were saved by Dot Pixis,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.82,0:00:47.66,Default - italics,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,the high commander of the \Nsouthern territories.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.43,0:00:54.21,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I think we should listen to them...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.00,0:02:33.00,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Icon \NThe Battle for Trost (7)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.35,0:02:35.38,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.82,0:02:37.84,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know whether \NI can seal the hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.71,0:02:41.34,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.72,0:02:47.17,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Well said.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.17,0:02:48.56,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,You're a real man.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.81,0:02:54.86,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I'll call my strategists. \NWe'll develop a plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.56,0:02:56.73,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.73,0:03:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That idea depends on \Nso many assumptions,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.03,0:03:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he's just going to run with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.20,0:03:04.12,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I was just thinking the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.31,0:03:07.31,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,But there's no sense in \Ndoubting his decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.03,0:03:12.37,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Commander Pixis must see potential \Nin something the rest of us can't see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.58,0:03:13.84,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,Something we can't see?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.25,0:03:17.66,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Also, I think there's a bigger \Nissue that must be addressed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.66,0:03:19.60,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,before the plan can be executed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.20,0:03:23.00,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,And the Commander fully recognizes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.53,0:03:24.64,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.30,0:03:27.77,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,The Titans aren't our only enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.12,0:03:30.77,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,There's no time to waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.76,0:03:38.28,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I will need your help, young soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.95,0:03:54.86,Default,Soldiers,0000,0000,0000,,A plan to retake Trost?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.86,0:03:55.99,Default,Soldiers,0000,0000,0000,,You're kidding...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.99,0:03:58.34,Default,Soldiers,0000,0000,0000,,We have no way to seal that hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.62,0:04:00.44,Default,Soldiers,0000,0000,0000,,What is the brass thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.44,0:04:02.39,Default,Soldiers,0000,0000,0000,,Going into Trost would be our deaths!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.39,0:04:04.05,Default,Soldiers,0000,0000,0000,,Since we can't seal the hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.05,0:04:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all we can do is die \Ndefending Wall Rose's gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.71,0:04:09.93,Default,Soldiers,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it... They want glory that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.41,0:04:13.99,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I have to return to that hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.69,0:04:17.48,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,No! I don't want to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.65,0:04:19.58,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see my family!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.58,0:04:21.30,Default,Ma,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Daz, you're being too loud...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.30,0:04:23.49,Default,Officer,0000,0000,0000,,You there! I heard you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.95,0:04:26.30,Default,Officer,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying you want to \Nabandon your mission?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.30,0:04:27.53,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.53,0:04:31.25,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,This is nothing but mass suicide! \NIt's meaningless!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.04,0:04:35.83,Default,Officer,0000,0000,0000,,Have you no respect for \Nhumanity? For order?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.38,0:04:39.67,Default,Officer,0000,0000,0000,,If I chose to, I could \Nexecute you this minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.43,0:04:41.66,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.05,0:04:45.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a hundred times better \Nthan being eaten by Titans!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.44,0:04:46.72,Default,Mar,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, Daz!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.72,0:04:48.21,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,No! Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.80,0:04:51.43,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I won't go back there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.22,0:04:54.06,Default,Soldiers,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.06,0:04:56.44,Default,Soldiers,0000,0000,0000,,Given the circumstances, \NI don't blame him...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.97,0:04:57.98,Default,Soldiers,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.98,0:05:00.27,Default,Soldiers,0000,0000,0000,,I hope someone rebels over here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.27,0:05:03.15,Default,Soldiers,0000,0000,0000,,I'd at least like to choose how I die.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.15,0:05:04.16,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.64,0:05:06.45,Default,Soldier,0000,0000,0000,,I-It was a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.78,0:05:07.82,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.53,0:05:10.03,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Be loud...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.03,0:05:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And get others to go along!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.93,0:05:16.46,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,In the Garrison, plenty of \Nus aren't happy, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.46,0:05:19.00,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We'll take advantage \Nof the chaos and leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.38,0:05:21.55,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,Leave and go where?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.38,0:05:24.59,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,To see my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.07,0:05:27.50,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually, this wall will also fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.51,0:05:32.47,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,They say that before Titans gained \Ndominion over the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.47,0:05:35.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there was endless slaughter of human life
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.67,0:05:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in wars over race and ideology...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.37,0:05:42.78,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Then someone said,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.40,0:05:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If a powerful external \Nthreat were to appear,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.03,0:05:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,humanity would cease \Nits wars and unite."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.37,0:05:53.91,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.50,0:05:56.79,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I've never heard that legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.25,0:06:00.13,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds naïve...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.47,0:06:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Almost silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.63,0:06:07.26,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,You have a warped mind like mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.55,0:06:09.37,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Even when that powerful threat
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.37,0:06:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has pushed us to the \Nbrink of destruction,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.85,0:06:14.89,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,we still have yet to unite.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.52,0:06:18.71,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,No, but it's high time we did so.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.06,0:06:21.72,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, we won't \Neven be able to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.34,0:06:30.44,Default,Ha,0000,0000,0000,,Eren?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.74,0:06:33.12,Default,Ha,0000,0000,0000,,He's safe, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.66,0:06:37.54,Default - italics,Ha,0000,0000,0000,,Focus on the mission?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.17,0:06:41.29,Default - italics,Ha,0000,0000,0000,,How dare he address a \Nsuperior officer that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.83,0:06:45.42,Default - italics,Ha,0000,0000,0000,,By the look of it, Mikasa and \NArmin must be safe, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.49,0:06:50.29,Default - italics,Ha,0000,0000,0000,,But what's Eren doing \Nwith the Commander?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.05,0:06:59.32,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,You want some?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.92,0:07:01.19,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.03,0:07:11.27,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Kill me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.27,0:07:12.82,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to \Nexecute me, do it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.82,0:07:14.78,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure? I'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.04,0:07:24.75,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Attention!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.13,0:07:35.64,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I shall now explain the \Nplan to retake Trost.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.37,0:07:38.64,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,For this mission, our objective
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.64,0:07:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is to seal the hole where \Nthe gate was destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.23,0:07:49.27,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Seal it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.71,0:07:51.28,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.97,0:07:54.16,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Let me introduce you to the one
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.16,0:07:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who will seal the hole for us...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.17,0:08:00.52,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,From the Trainee Corps, Eren Jaeger.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.33,0:08:04.09,Default,Co,0000,0000,0000,,E-Eren!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.13,0:08:07.88,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,He is the result of a top-secret project
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.88,0:08:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to turn humans into Titans.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.26,0:08:17.34,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,He can create and \Ncontrol a Titan's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.74,0:08:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.65,0:08:23.16,Default,Co,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea what the \NCommander's talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.16,0:08:25.44,Default,Co,0000,0000,0000,,Am I just too stupid to get it or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.44,0:08:27.82,Default,Freckles,0000,0000,0000,,Would you shut up, idiot?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.09,0:08:30.87,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,He will become a Titan,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.87,0:08:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,pick up the giant boulder \Nby the shattered gate,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.91,0:08:37.38,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,carry it over, and seal the hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.80,0:08:40.37,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Your job will be
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.30,0:08:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to protect him from Titans \Nwhile he moves the boulder!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.48,0:08:49.63,Default,Gus,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have to fight the Titans?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.77,0:08:51.52,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,E-Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.52,0:08:54.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mean any disrespect by \Nspeaking up to a ranking officer...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.28,0:08:56.50,Default,Gus,0000,0000,0000,,No, continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.50,0:08:57.89,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.34,0:09:02.39,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,Titans are typically drawn to pursue\Nthe largest number of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.11,0:09:05.54,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,If we can take advantage of that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.54,0:09:07.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to lure them along the walls,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.85,0:09:10.29,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,we can draw most of them away from Eren
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.29,0:09:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,without engaging them in direct combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.22,0:09:15.92,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,And by using the cannons against those
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.92,0:09:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lured away, we'll \Nminimize our own losses.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.76,0:09:23.60,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,But since we can't \Nleave Eren undefended,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.60,0:09:26.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a small elite force should protect him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.39,0:09:31.69,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,And we can't avoid engaging the \NTitans that come through the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.69,0:09:34.32,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,The skills of the elite \Nforce will be critical.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.75,0:09:36.19,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,All right, understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.19,0:09:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll take that into account \Nand revise our plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.41,0:09:42.53,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,But this will only work if \NEren can carry that boulder
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.53,0:09:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and seal the hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.20,0:09:48.95,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,We are proceeding with the operation \Nwithout certain proof that he can.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.95,0:09:51.44,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot help but feel doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.75,0:09:55.04,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, given the uncertainty \Nof a crucial element,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.04,0:09:58.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not relish sending many \Nmen to their deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.51,0:10:01.97,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But I do understand what \NCommander Pixis is thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.51,0:10:03.34,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.34,0:10:04.95,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,The first issue is one of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.81,0:10:09.25,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,Even as we speak, Titans continue \Nto enter the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.89,0:10:15.12,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,The greater their numbers in Trost, \Nthe worse our odds of success in retaking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.12,0:10:19.95,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And the higher the chance \Nof Wall Rose falling...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.65,0:10:22.11,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,And one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.99,0:10:28.42,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,There's a limit to how much one \Ncan be motivated by terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.17,0:10:33.36,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Lift that giant rock?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.83,0:10:35.08,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Is it possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.77,0:10:38.41,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Has humanity finally learned \Nto control the Titans?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.41,0:10:39.91,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You're lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.91,0:10:43.28,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I won't put my life on the line for \Na plan I can't even understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.76,0:10:46.01,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think we are?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.01,0:10:47.10,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,We aren't...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.10,0:10:49.54,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,We aren't pawns for you to sacrifice!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.05,0:10:51.59,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,A human weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.59,0:10:53.31,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,He's lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.31,0:10:54.35,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,He thinks we're fools!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.35,0:10:56.27,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,He's telling us to die here, today!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.27,0:10:57.48,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,I'm leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.11,0:11:02.11,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.40,0:11:03.22,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,And me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.78,0:11:05.03,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,I'm out of here, as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.22,0:11:06.16,Default,Officer,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.16,0:11:07.94,Default,Officer,0000,0000,0000,,You'll get the death penalty for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.91,0:11:11.86,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'll spend humanity's last \Nhours with my family!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.83,0:11:14.21,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.21,0:11:15.21,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.21,0:11:17.36,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't do something, \Nthere will be chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.38,0:11:21.03,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Ready to die, traitors?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.32,0:11:22.95,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,I'll kill you right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.23,0:11:26.74,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Here is my decision!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.33,0:11:30.50,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I shall pardon anyone who deserts now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.52,0:11:35.09,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Once you succumb to the Titans' fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.09,0:11:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you can never fight them again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.02,0:11:41.73,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Those who have learned \Nthat fear should leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.63,0:11:47.91,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,And anyone wishing their \Nparents, siblings,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.91,0:11:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and loved ones to feel that \Nfear should also leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.78,0:12:02.52,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.13,0:12:05.78,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.18,0:12:08.53,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,My daughter is my...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.19,0:12:13.95,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,My last hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.37,0:12:18.55,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Let me tell you what \Nhappened four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.29,0:12:21.71,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,About our attempt to retake Wall Maria.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.47,0:12:25.90,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,As I'm sure you're all aware,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.84,0:12:29.68,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,that operation was no more \Nthan the government's way
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.68,0:12:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of dealing with its inability \Nto feed all of the unemployed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.80,0:12:35.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a culling.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.40,0:12:40.44,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,The reason no one speaks \Nof it is because
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.44,0:12:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by sending them outside \Nthese cramped walls,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.19,0:12:47.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we were able to survive within them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.49,0:12:55.21,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,All of humanity, including myself, \Nbears the weight of that sin!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.83,0:12:58.67,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Because so few escaped Wall Maria,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.05,0:13:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there was never any open rebellion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.78,0:13:03.73,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,But what about now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.54,0:13:06.79,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,If Wall Rose falls,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.79,0:13:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the sacrifice will be more \Nthan just twenty percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.76,0:13:13.95,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,The territory within Wall Sina
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.95,0:13:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,won't support even half \Nthe remaining population.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.35,0:13:19.25,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,If humanity falls,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.25,0:13:22.75,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,it won't be because we were \Ndevoured by the Titans.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.63,0:13:26.73,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,It will be because we killed each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.93,0:13:31.17,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,We must not die even \Ndeeper within the walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.70,0:13:34.20,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I beg of you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.92,0:13:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to die right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.84,0:13:49.58,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if I can use the \NTitan's power to lift that boulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.37,0:13:53.43,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,But I understand what I must do...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.40,0:13:56.44,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,It may be a lie,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.79,0:13:59.96,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,but I must make it happen anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.77,0:14:04.53,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,I must become a symbol
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.21,0:14:08.76,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,of hope for everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.95,0:14:14.95,Eyecatch1A,E,0000,0000,0000,,Information We Can Share So Far:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.95,0:14:14.95,Eyecatch1,E,0000,0000,0000,,3D Maneuver Gear Weight-Shifting Device (1) \N\NTo maneuver in 3D space, it's necessary \Nto be able to shift one's weight precisely, \Nusing belts strung all over the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.95,0:14:19.96,Eyecatch2A,E,0000,0000,0000,,Information We Can Share So Far:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.95,0:14:19.96,Eyecatch2,E,0000,0000,0000,,3D Maneuver Gear Weight-Shifting Device (2) \N\NTo allow quick maneuvers in \N3D space, the equipment has \Nbeen made as light as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.87,0:14:25.46,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I see you're all here...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.92,0:14:27.89,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,You have one mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.41,0:14:30.47,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,To guard Eren Jaeger,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.97,0:14:34.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,eliminating any threat that \Nappears during the operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.00,0:14:39.07,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,It will be the most dangerous and \Ndifficult task in the entire operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.90,0:14:42.38,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,It's no exaggeration
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.38,0:14:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to say that humanity's fate \Nrests on your shoulders.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.41,0:14:48.79,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,Commander, may I say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.06,0:14:49.99,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.67,0:14:54.28,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,Does this human weapon really work?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.28,0:14:55.30,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet, Riko!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.66,0:14:57.75,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,You don't believe it, either, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.45,0:15:01.91,Default,Mitabi,0000,0000,0000,,Commander, this operation \Ndepends on Eren Jaeger,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.91,0:15:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and we know nothing about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.85,0:15:08.84,Default,Mitabi,0000,0000,0000,,If he cannot function, many soldiers \Nwill have died for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.44,0:15:12.01,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.40,0:15:15.26,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really enjoy losing to \Nthe Titans that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.14,0:15:18.97,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.97,0:15:21.80,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I hate losing more than anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.75,0:15:27.28,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,But unfortunately, I've been \Nlosing for my entire life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.13,0:15:32.50,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I want to win against the Titans...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.16,0:15:35.23,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I want to beat those giant freaks
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.23,0:15:37.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,more than anything in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.66,0:15:40.25,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,S-So do we!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.50,0:15:43.88,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Then betting on him is our only option.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.40,0:15:47.76,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, we know nothing about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.58,0:15:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he's the only chance we \Nhave to defeat the Titans.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.86,0:15:56.97,Default,Gus,0000,0000,0000,,Commander, it's time for the \Ndecoy operation to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.51,0:16:00.98,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Ian Dietrich,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.41,0:16:02.85,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Riko Brzenska,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.28,0:16:04.46,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Mitabi Jarnach...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.96,0:16:09.23,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,You are the Garrison's \Nmost elite troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.19,0:16:12.40,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I'm entrusting humanity's fate to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.92,0:16:13.83,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.48,0:16:17.18,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Ian, you take command.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.71,0:16:19.95,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,You have full authority out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.21,0:16:22.96,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.57,0:16:24.90,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I have no objections.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.90,0:16:25.81,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Nor do I.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.32,0:16:28.61,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm not capable...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.61,0:16:29.71,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.91,0:16:32.97,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,You're a man who knows his drinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.39,0:16:37.66,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,You're well-acquainted with \Ndrink both bitter and sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.93,0:16:39.97,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.70,0:16:42.73,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.98,0:16:45.96,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,Eren, I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.37,0:16:51.29,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,I ended up making you \Nresponsible for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.29,0:16:52.95,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,It's like I said before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.23,0:16:55.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have the ability to \Nfind the right answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.56,0:16:58.03,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I believe in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.31,0:16:59.83,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Eren, I'm going to—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.83,0:17:01.37,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you're going \Nto come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.44,0:17:04.77,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,You've been assigned to the decoy team.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.09,0:17:08.00,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't leave you alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.00,0:17:08.98,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,If you're alone, you'll—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.98,0:17:10.30,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.93,0:17:13.69,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not your little \Nbrother or a child...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.69,0:17:15.09,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I told you that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.93,0:17:18.87,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Ackerman,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.15,0:17:22.45,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,join the elite force protecting Jaeger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.13,0:17:25.59,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,We need your skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.34,0:17:28.26,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go... It's time!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.82,0:17:31.82,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Bye, Armin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.34,0:17:33.44,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Don't die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.90,0:17:35.65,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.52,0:17:52.05,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,A top-secret human weapon, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.05,0:17:54.13,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you can seal that hole, \Nit doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.13,0:17:55.76,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Our priority is to protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.14,0:17:56.88,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,We're counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.59,0:17:58.55,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.66,0:18:01.55,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Eren, are you feeling okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.55,0:18:02.56,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.26,0:18:05.00,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Eren...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.00,0:18:07.00,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I said I'm fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.00,0:18:09.45,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Much better than when \Nwe were surrounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.45,0:18:11.37,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We aren't playing house here, Jaeger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.08,0:18:13.57,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.00,0:18:16.07,Default,Mitabi,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe we have to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.07,0:18:18.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,leave humanity's fate up \Nto a spoiled kid like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.59,0:18:22.31,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Enough, guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.31,0:18:23.99,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,We'll soon reach the shortest \Nroute to the boulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.49,0:18:27.80,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not seeing any Titans...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.16,0:18:30.44,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone must have succeeded \Nin luring them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.00,0:18:35.16,Default,Leader,0000,0000,0000,,Listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.16,0:18:37.55,Default,Leader,0000,0000,0000,,You only need to get them \Nto the edge of town!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.80,0:18:39.64,Default,Leader,0000,0000,0000,,Avoid unnecessary combat!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.18,0:18:44.06,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Jaeger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.56,0:18:50.30,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,During this operation, \Nmore than just a few will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.65,0:18:51.98,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,For you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.15,0:18:58.81,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,They will be our fellows, \Nranked both above and below us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.51,0:19:02.32,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,As soldiers, they're \Nprepared to die, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.33,0:19:07.08,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,But they are not pawns without a voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.45,0:19:11.58,Default,Leader,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.29,0:19:16.46,Default,Leader,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.98,0:19:19.38,Default,Leader,0000,0000,0000,,A little more...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.53,0:19:22.43,Default,Leader,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.65,0:19:27.42,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,They have names and families.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.85,0:19:30.10,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,And all the feelings that those entail.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.64,0:19:35.00,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,Alyosha, Dominic, Phine, Isabel,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.00,0:19:38.57,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,Ludwig, Martina, Guido, Hans...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.97,0:19:41.78,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,They're all humans as \Nalive as either of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.86,0:19:46.36,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,I've known some of them \Nsince my trainee days.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.12,0:19:52.17,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,And today, many will die for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.37,0:19:58.41,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,You have a responsibility to ensure that \Ntheir deaths will mean something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.27,0:20:00.72,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.26,0:20:04.92,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,Never let yourself forget that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.92,0:20:07.68,Default,Riko,0000,0000,0000,,And be prepared to die \Nfor that responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.43,0:20:09.48,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.55,0:20:11.59,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.09,0:20:13.98,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make this happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.96,0:20:22.98,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Since the Titans appeared, \Nhumanity has never won against them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.77,0:20:26.88,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Their continuous advance has meant
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.88,0:20:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,humanity's continuous retreat \Nand loss of territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.21,0:20:35.58,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,But when this mission succeeds,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.20,0:20:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,humanity will have retaken \Nits territory from them
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.44,0:20:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for the very first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.68,0:20:43.52,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.52,0:20:44.13,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.78,0:20:51.52,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,This will be humanity's first \Nvictory against the Titans!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.75,0:21:04.41,Default,An,0000,0000,0000,,Green smoke round, confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.92,0:21:07.59,Default,An,0000,0000,0000,,The elite force has begun the mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.19,0:21:16.79,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Compared to all that humanity has lost, \Nit may seem insignificant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.92,0:21:25.24,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,But for humanity, that step will be a great \Nadvance in our attack on the Titans!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.45,0:21:58.50,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt a human of that size
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.29,0:22:01.71,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,could lift that boulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.51,0:22:06.51,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,But I believe Eren has the \Nstrength to lead us forward...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.83,0:22:15.72,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Eren?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.15,0:23:56.01,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,The operation to retake Trost has begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.73,0:23:58.95,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,As many soldiers die,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.95,0:24:01.17,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Eren, now a Titan, loses control
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.17,0:24:03.49,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,and destroys his own head.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.49,0:24:06.08,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,The operation seems \Nto have failed, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.98,0:27:39.63,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Wound \NThe Battle for Trost (8)
